<hl>
<seg id=1> Xiaotong Fei Awarded Megsaisai Prize </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Manila, August 31st. Doctor Xiaotong Fei,the famous sociologist and Deputy President of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, was awarded the 1994 Megsaisai Community Leadership Prize here in Manila this afternoon. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The awards ceremony was held at the the Philippines Cultural Center. </seg>
<seg id=4> President Ramos attended the ceremony and awarded medals, monetary awards, and certificates to the six outstanding recipients. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> In his acceptance speech, Fei Xiaotong said, "I will never be discouraged given by our friendly neighbor country.  As long as I live,I will make full use of every minute to benefit the people of Asia as well as people all over the world.  so that the knowledge accumulated by human being can create an even more beautiful society." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> -Ramond Megsaisai Prize which was named after the former president of the Philippines is renowned as the Asian Nobel Prize. </seg>
<seg id=7> This prize has five awards, issued once per year to the individuals and institutes that have made a great contribution in the fields of governmental service, public service, community leadership, press, literature, and creative communication are as well as international understanding. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> 172 individuals and 14 institutes have been awarded the prize since its introduction in 1958. </seg>
</p>
